"n.特殊能力；窍门 【记】 knock的变体，意为敲 开脑袋→开窍 【例】 He has a knack of making friends wherever he goes. n. 诀窍; 窍门 【记】源于: knock的变体, 就是敲开脑袋, 让人开窍－窍门读: NIKE, 因为有了商业窍门才会成功. 【参】knocker(n 门环) 【反】foolishness(n 愚蠢) 【记】knock 敲，开，一敲就开的窍门 knack (n.)  mid-14c., ""deception, trick, device,"" of uncertain origin, probably from a Low German word meaning ""a sharp sounding blow"" (compare Middle English knak, late 14c.; German knacken ""to crack""), of imitative origin. Sense of ""special skill"" is first recorded 1580s, if this is in fact the same word."
